<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
When compiled for GNU/Linux (__linux__ defined) the #ifndef __linux__ block is excluded so 'ret' remains initialized to -1 and is not modified. The controlling expression (0 >= ret) therefore always evaluates to true (invariant) and the if-statement is constant — this violates Rule 14.3. (On non-Linux builds where sysctl/sysctlbyname may update ret the expression is not necessarily invariant.)
</scenario>

